        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         For the uninitiated: that green guy is a CryptoPunk. CryptoPunks are 24 x 24 pixel art NFTs, of which there are, and will only ever be, 10,000. CryptoPunks, created by
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OwyAMhU9TlhE_ISELFrOZa0TEuClTAhE4HfX2Q5PFSAhknuzn94EjXHN52z1XYp9rpveONuFvjUiEhR0Vyxy8FYM0SvcT87b3wmjDQp3vBXFzIVoqB7L9WGIARyGns4NzqdnDynGcAIx3ABNwpWWv-GCcb9-4cNCXrzt8wARo8YXlnROyaB9Ee72pr5v8bie68nLRLbWDvLV6L_kHgWJoqwcruRTc8ElILfqhE91dT71ABHmfQICTRi44Dt4IbUyPoG8931bZ1WOp5OD5GcqKTZmWXEJam_x8uA3jKbRoc3u3IwV6z5jcEtFfqemCd3KYV0xYGlQ_OzqRaaG0MFyoK2XDoqbRCKkMa84-t670b_oHlBuGZg" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Larva Labs
         </a>
         in June 2017,\xc2\xa0 are OG NFTs. As new NFT projects pop up hourly, CryptoPunks are scarce and valuable by nature of their age.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         So as NFT values have soared over the past couple of weeks, CryptoPunks have led the charge. The most expensive Punk sold for 4.2k ETH in March. Today it\xe2\x80\x99s worth $7.57 million USD. If you want to buy your very own Punk right now, the cheapest on offer will cost you 51.85 ETH. That\xe2\x80\x99s the \xe2\x80\x9cfloor price.\xe2\x80\x9d You\xe2\x80\x99ll get a more common Punk at that price. To buy a rare Punk, an Ape, Alien, or Zombie, like the one seen above, you\xe2\x80\x99re going to have to fork over a whole lot more ETH.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         A few other things to know about CryptoPunks:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Owning a Punk is a status symbol, like owning a Ferrari or an expensive handbag.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Punk owners often use the image of their Punk as their profile picture (PFP).
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           Displaying a Punk that you don\xe2\x80\x99t own as your profile picture is frowned upon.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         This weekend, hundreds of people changed their profile picture to that one single Zombie Punk, which sold for 1,201.725 ETH ($3.75 million) at auction on Friday. No one frowned upon so many people displaying the Punk, wearing a deconstructed party hat emoji, because they all owned it.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         For Friday\xe2\x80\x99s auction, 478 people joined forces on
